ies and provides the full range of inflection and formation of words in German. It also covers the structure of the ›small‹ parts of speech and takes into account historical developments as well as the formation of foreign words. The presentation is oriented particularly on the new study curricula and is separated into introductory and advanced chapters. It is supplemented by numerous examples and problem-oriented discussions, exercises and sample solutions as well as references and an extensive glossary to facilitate exam preparation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexMorphologyxStudy and teaching. 4aDeutsch/Sprachlehrbücher. 4aLinguistik. 4aMorphologie (Sprache). 4aWortbildung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGerman / Language Textbooks.  aLinguistics.  aMorphology (Language).  aWord Formation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2011z9783110261189oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2011z9783110261240oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311023791740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311023790040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110237900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110237900/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2011  aZDB-23-DGGb2011  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014